---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'SafetyWing in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-warning', text: 'Visa Compliance Warning', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-types', text: 'Coverage Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'using-in-spain', text: 'Using SafetyWing in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose SafetyWing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'alternatives', text: 'When to Choose Something Else', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Spain', href: '/countries/spain/insurance' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing vs Cigna', href: '/compare/safetywing-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'benefit', header: 'Benefit' },
  { key: 'nomad', header: 'Nomad Insurance' },
  { key: 'remote', header: 'Remote Health' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { benefit: 'Type', nomad: 'Travel Medical', remote: 'Health Insurance' },
  { benefit: 'Maximum Coverage', nomad: '$250,000', remote: '$1M-$10M' },
  { benefit: 'Outpatient', nomad: 'Emergency only', remote: 'Full coverage' },
  { benefit: 'Routine Care', nomad: 'Not covered', remote: 'Covered' },
  { benefit: 'Mental Health', nomad: 'Not covered', remote: 'Included' },
  { benefit: 'Pre-existing', nomad: 'Not covered', remote: 'After waiting period' },
  { benefit: 'Visa Compliant', nomad: 'Usually not', remote: 'Possibly' },
  { benefit: 'Commitment', nomad: 'None (cancel anytime)', remote: 'Monthly' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'age', header: 'Age' },
  { key: 'nomad', header: 'Nomad Insurance' },
  { key: 'remote', header: 'Remote Health' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { age: '25-39', nomad: '$45/4 weeks (~$49/mo)', remote: '$100-200/mo' },
  { age: '40-49', nomad: '$76/4 weeks (~$83/mo)', remote: '$150-300/mo' },
  { age: '50-59', nomad: '$117/4 weeks (~$127/mo)', remote: '$250-450/mo' },
  { age: '60-69', nomad: '$189/4 weeks (~$205/mo)', remote: '$400-700/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="SafetyWing Insurance in Spain"
  description="Guide to using SafetyWing in Spain. Affordable nomad coverage with important limitations. Visa compliance, coverage details, and who it's right for."
  headline="SafetyWing Insurance in Spain"
  subheadline="The digital nomad favorite. Affordable and flexible—but understand its limitations before relying on it in Spain."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/spain-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a SafetyWing Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/safetywing"
>
  <h2 id="overview">SafetyWing in Spain</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing has become the go-to insurance for digital nomads, and Spain—with its Digital Nomad Visa—attracts plenty of them. But before you choose SafetyWing for Spain, you need to understand what it is and isn't.
  </p>
  <p>
    SafetyWing offers two products: <strong>Nomad Insurance</strong> (travel medical) and <strong>Remote Health</strong> (actual health insurance). Most people know Nomad Insurance—the cheap, subscription-based option. But Nomad Insurance may not work for Spanish visa requirements.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$45</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Per 4 weeks (Nomad, age 30)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">180+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Countries covered</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">0</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Commitment required</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-warning">Visa Compliance Warning</h2>

  <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-900 mb-2">Important: Visa Requirements</h3>
    <p class="text-red-800">
      <strong>SafetyWing Nomad Insurance typically does NOT meet Spanish visa requirements.</strong> It's travel medical insurance with limited coverage, not the comprehensive health insurance most visas require. If you're applying for a Non-Lucrative Visa, Digital Nomad Visa, or other long-term visa, you likely need a different insurer.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3>Why Nomad Insurance May Not Work for Visas</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Coverage type:</strong> Travel medical, not health insurance</li>
    <li><strong>Maximum coverage:</strong> $250,000—may not meet minimums</li>
    <li><strong>No routine care:</strong> Visas often require outpatient coverage</li>
    <li><strong>No copay guarantee:</strong> Many visas require zero-copay plans</li>
    <li><strong>Not EU-regulated:</strong> Some consulates prefer EU insurers</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Remote Health May Work</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing's <strong>Remote Health</strong> product is actual health insurance with comprehensive coverage. It may meet visa requirements, but verify with your specific consulate. Remote Health costs more than Nomad Insurance—$100-700/month depending on age and coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Visa Recommendation</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      For Spanish visa applications, consider <a href="/countries/spain/insurance/axa-global" class="underline">AXA Global</a> or <a href="/countries/spain/insurance/allianz-care" class="underline">Allianz Care</a> (EU-regulated) or <a href="/countries/spain/insurance/cigna-global" class="underline">Cigna Global</a>. Once your visa is approved and you're established in Spain, you can evaluate if SafetyWing meets your ongoing needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-types">Coverage Options</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing offers two very different products. Understanding the difference is critical.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance (Travel Medical)</h3>
  <p>
    This is SafetyWing's famous product—the one all the nomad bloggers talk about. It covers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Emergency medical treatment</li>
    <li>Acute illness that arises while traveling</li>
    <li>Accidents and injuries</li>
    <li>Emergency dental (pain relief only, up to $1,000)</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation up to $100,000</li>
    <li>Lost baggage, travel delays</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>What Nomad Insurance Doesn't Cover</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Routine doctor visits</li>
    <li>Ongoing prescriptions</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions (at all)</li>
    <li>Mental health</li>
    <li>Maternity</li>
    <li>Dental (except emergency)</li>
    <li>Preventive care</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Remote Health (Full Health Insurance)</h3>
  <p>
    Remote Health is comprehensive health insurance—a completely different product:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Coverage up to $10 million</li>
    <li>Full outpatient care</li>
    <li>Mental health included</li>
    <li>Maternity available (12-month wait)</li>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions (24-month wait)</li>
    <li>Routine care, prescriptions, preventive care</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Understand What You're Buying"
    description="Make sure you choose the right SafetyWing product for your needs."
    buttonText="Learn More"
    buttonHref="/go/safetywing"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing's pricing is simple and transparent—one of its main advantages.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Nomad Insurance Pricing</h3>
  <p>
    Billed every 4 weeks with no commitment:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Age-based pricing only</li>
    <li>$250 deductible per incident</li>
    <li>One child under 10 free per adult</li>
    <li>Cancel anytime—no penalties</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Remote Health Pricing</h3>
  <p>
    Monthly billing with more variables:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Age affects pricing significantly</li>
    <li>Deductible options: $0-$5,000</li>
    <li>Coverage area affects price</li>
    <li>Higher premiums but comprehensive coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="using-in-spain">Using SafetyWing in Spain</h2>

  <h3>Finding Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing doesn't have a traditional provider network in Spain. You can see any licensed provider:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Private hospitals and clinics</li>
    <li>English-speaking doctors (common in expat areas)</li>
    <li>Urgent care centers</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
    <li>Pay the Spanish provider upfront</li>
    <li>Get itemized receipt (factura)</li>
    <li>Submit claim via SafetyWing portal</li>
    <li>Wait 10-30 days for reimbursement</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    Direct billing is limited. Expect to pay and file for reimbursement for most care.
  </p>

  <h3>Emergency Hospitalization</h3>
  <p>
    For major emergencies, SafetyWing coordinates with hospitals. Contact them as soon as possible. They can arrange direct billing for significant hospital stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Spanish Healthcare Costs</h3>
  <p>
    Good news: Spanish private healthcare is affordable. If you're using Nomad Insurance for emergencies only:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Doctor visit: €50-100</li>
    <li>Specialist: €80-150</li>
    <li>Urgent care: €100-200</li>
    <li>Hospital day: €500-1,500</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You can pay for routine care out of pocket affordably and use SafetyWing for emergencies—if you're healthy and don't need a visa-compliant policy.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose SafetyWing</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Nomad Insurance Good For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Young, healthy travelers (under 40)</li>
        <li>Digital nomads passing through</li>
        <li>Short-term stays (not visa-dependent)</li>
        <li>Those on tourist visas</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious without health needs</li>
        <li>People testing the nomad lifestyle</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Remote Health Good For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
        <li>Long-term expats wanting budget option</li>
        <li>Those who want comprehensive coverage</li>
        <li>People with mental health needs</li>
        <li>Possible visa compliance (verify)</li>
        <li>Subscription model preference</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="alternatives">When to Choose Something Else</h2>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose a Different Insurer If:</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
      <li><strong>You need a Spanish visa</strong> — Nomad Insurance likely won't work</li>
      <li><strong>You have pre-existing conditions</strong> — Not covered by Nomad</li>
      <li><strong>You're over 50</strong> — Consider more comprehensive coverage</li>
      <li><strong>You need mental health care</strong> — Nomad doesn't cover it</li>
      <li><strong>You want direct billing</strong> — SafetyWing is mostly reimbursement</li>
      <li><strong>You're settling long-term</strong> — Spanish or EU insurers may be better value</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Better Options for Spain Visas</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/countries/spain/insurance/axa-global">AXA Global</a> — EU-regulated, smooth visa process</li>
    <li><a href="/countries/spain/insurance/allianz-care">Allianz Care</a> — Good value, EU-regulated</li>
    <li><a href="/countries/spain/insurance/cigna-global">Cigna Global</a> — Large network, visa-compliant</li>
    <li><a href="/countries/spain/insurance/bupa-global">BUPA Global</a> — Premium option</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Right Choice for You?"
    description="Compare SafetyWing with comprehensive options for Spain."
    buttonText="Compare All Options"
    buttonHref="/countries/spain/insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Can I use SafetyWing for the Spain Digital Nomad Visa?</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Nomad Insurance likely won't qualify.</strong> The Digital Nomad Visa requires comprehensive health insurance with specific coverage minimums. Remote Health may work—verify with your consulate before applying.
  </p>

  <h3>Is SafetyWing enough for living in Spain?</h3>
  <p>
    It depends on your situation. Nomad Insurance covers emergencies only. If you're young, healthy, and okay paying for routine care out of pocket, it can work as emergency backup. For comprehensive healthcare needs, it's not enough.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I switch from SafetyWing to another insurer later?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. SafetyWing has no cancellation penalties. You can cancel anytime and switch to a comprehensive insurer. However, be aware that switching may require new medical underwriting—pre-existing conditions may be excluded.
  </p>

  <h3>Does SafetyWing cover EU healthcare?</h3>
  <p>
    SafetyWing covers private healthcare in Spain and Europe. It doesn't replace EHIC or public healthcare access. For Spanish public healthcare (seguridad social), you need to qualify through residency/employment.
  </p>

  <h3>What's the SafetyWing claims experience like?</h3>
  <p>
    Mixed reviews. Simple claims process online, but some users report delays and denied claims requiring appeals. Document everything and don't expect the premium service of traditional insurers.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Understand Your Options"
    description="Make an informed choice for your Spain insurance needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Visa requirements and coverage details change. SafetyWing's Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance, not comprehensive health insurance. Verify visa requirements with Spanish authorities before relying on any insurance for visa applications.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
